The paper deals with the problem of signal parameter estimation from measurements acquired by a low-complexity analog-to-digital converter (ADC) with 1-bit output resolution and an unknown quantization threshold. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT), control systems (cs.SY), networked systems (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SP), and multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) systems (cs.MM). Therefore, these are the likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
